titleStmt.title: Variants of the negated existential particle
titleStmt.author: Johanna Doppelbauer

sourceDesc.p: This is the feature file for the negated existential particle.

revisionDesc.change: For EGY-___ there are no values found

wib:featureValueObservation.note: With the preposition fiy, ma has the alternate form ma(a)fīš there is not.
since the existential bī is also reported, it can be deducted that the negative form for it is mābi
One instance of mā bīš was also recorded.
Elicted from examples. The exact example was mā-fā-hā-š ´there isn´t in it/her´.
Originally, mā-hast, mā-miš and mā-šay also exist alongside the Pan-Arabic and much more dominant mā-fīh.
mā-hast is not as common in Kuwait as it is in Bahrain
Refers to the near deixis: there is not here
Refers to the far deixis: there is not there
it is now sometimes replaced by the koiné form mā fīš
